e, England"},"cs":{"about 1224–1249":"okolo 1224–1249","1222–1283":"1222–1283","1242–Male":"1242–Zesnulý","1244–Female":"1244–Zesnulá","1245–1312":"1245–1312","1224–1249":"1224–1249","1249":"1249","about 1239":"okolo 1239","1224":"1224","1312":"1312","1245":"1245","1244":"1244","1222":"1222","about 1224":"okolo 1224","1242":"1242","about 1244":"okolo 1244","1283":"1283","of Beeston, Cheshire, England":"Beeston, Cheshire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Beeston, Cheshire, England":"Beeston, Cheshire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Beeston, Yorkshire, England":"Beeston, Yorkshire, Anglie"},"da":{"about 1224–1249":"omkring 1224–1249","1222–1283":"1222–1283","1242–Male":"1242–Afdød","1244–Female":"1244–Afdød","1245–1312":"1245–1312","1224–1249":"1224–1249","1249":"1249","about 1239":"omkring 1239","1224":"1224","1312":"1312","1245":"1245","1244":"1244","1222":"1222","about 1224":"omkring 1224","1242":"1242","about 1244":"omkring 1244","1283":"1283","of Beeston, Cheshire, England":"Beeston, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Beeston, Cheshire, England":"Beeston, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Beeston, Yorkshire, England":"Beeston, Jórvík, England"},"nl":{"about 1224–1249":"circa 1224–1249","1222–1283":"1222–1283","1242–Male":"1242–Overleden","1244–Female":"1244–Overleden","1245–1312":"1245–1312","1224–1249":"1224–1249","1249":"1249","about 1239":"circa 1239","1224":"1224","1312":"1312","1245":"1245","1244":"1244","1222":"1222","about 1224":"circa 1224","1242":"1242","about 1244":"circa 1244","1283":"1283","of Beeston, Cheshire, England":"Beeston, Cheshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Beeston, Cheshire, England":"Beeston, Cheshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Beeston, Yorkshire, England":"Beeston, Yorkshire, England"},"en":{"about 1224–1249":"about 1224–1249","1222–1283":"1222–1283","1242–Male":"1242–Deceased","1244–Female":"1244–Deceased","1245–1312":"1245–1312","1224–1249":"1224–1249","1249":"1249","about 1239":"about 1239","1224":"1224","1312":"1312","1245":"1245","1244":"1244","1222":"1222","about 1224":"about 1224","1242":"1242","about 1244":"about 1244","1283":"1283","of Beeston, Cheshire, England":"Beeston, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Beeston, Cheshire, England":"Beeston, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Beeston, Yorkshire, England":"Beeston, Yorkshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Beeston","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English:","habitational name from any of the many places in England so called. Those in Nottinghamshire, Norfolk, and Yorkshire were settlements where bent grass grew (Old English <i>bēos</i> ‘rough grass’ + Old English <i>tūn</i> ‘enclosure, settlement’). In Bedfordshire it probably denoted a settlement on a bend (Old English <i>byge</i> + genitive singular <i>-es</i> + <i>tūn</i>). The hamlet stands on a marked bend of the river Yvel. In Cheshire it is named from a rock, below which trading took place (Old English <i>byge</i> ‘commerce’ + Old English <i>stān</i> ‘stone’). The reference is to a prominent crag where the remains of Beeston Castle stand. Compare   Beaston   and   Beeson  .","occasionally a topographic name for someone who lived in that part of a village known in Middle English as <i>bi este toun</i> ‘(place) at the east (end) of the village’."],"variants":[{"name":"Beston","meanings":["English: variant of   Beeston   and   Beaston  ."]},{"name":"Beeson","meanings":["English: variant of   Beeston  , a habitational name from a place called Beeston. The spelling reflects the local pronunciation of the Nottinghamshire placename, although this form is now quite widespread in England."]},{"name":"Beaston","meanings":["English: variant of   Beeston   (the more common form of the surname in England), a habitational name from any of various places called Beeston."]}]},{"name":"Margery","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual medieval vernacular form of   Margaret   (now also commonly spelled   Marjorie  ). This form of the name is preserved in the nursery rhyme ‘See-saw, Margery Daw’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705188,"age":0,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Margery Beeston was born about 1224, in Beeston, Yorkshire, England. She married Henry de Beeston about 1239, in Beeston, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. She died in 1249, in Beeston, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 26."},"et":{"about 1224–1249":"umbes 1224–1249","1222–1283":"1222–1283","1242–Male":"1242–Surnud","1244–Female":"1244–Surnud","1245–1312":"1245–1312","1224–1249":"1224–1249","1249":"1249","about 1239":"umbes 1239","1224":"1224","1312":"1312","1245":"1245","1244":"1244","1222":"1222","about 1224":"umbes 1224","1242":"1242","about 1244":"umbes 1244","1283":"1283","of Beeston, Cheshire, England":"Beeston, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Beeston, Cheshire, England":"Beeston, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Beeston, Yorkshire, England":"Beeston, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1224–1249":"noin 1224–1249","1222–1283":"1222–1283","1242–Male":"1242–Kuollut","1244–Female":"1244–Kuollut","1245–1312":"1245–1312","1224–1249":"1224–1249","1249":"1249","about 1239":"noin 1239","1224":"1224","1312":"1312","1245":"1245","1244":"1244","1222":"1222","about 1224":"noin 1224","1242":"1242","about 1244":"noin 1244","1283":"1283","of Beeston, Cheshire, England":"Beeston, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Beeston, Cheshire, England":"Beeston, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Beeston, Yorkshire, England":"Beeston, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"about 1224–1249":"environ 1224–1249","1222–1283":"1222–1283","1242–Male":"1242–Déc